The paper presents a software tool for automated time-series analysis, which involves feature extraction and selection. This is a common problem in machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories, as they cover general topics related to automated data analysis. cs.CE (Computational Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also relevant, as they often involve time-series analysis in specific applications. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant if the paper discusses time-series analysis in the context of network data.
